headline: BlackRock Group Buys Aligned Data Centers in $40 Billion Deal
summary: BlackRock's new artificial intelligence infrastructure consortium has struck its first deal, and it's a big one.  The group, led by BlackRock's Global Infrastructure Partners, agreed to acquire Aligned Data Centers in a deal that values the company at $40 billion including debt, the companies said Wednesday.  BlackRock announced its AI infrastructure fund last year, with partners including Microsoft, Mubadala Investment Co.’s MGX, the Kuwait Investment Authority, and Singapore's Temasek.

The acquisition comes amid a flurry of deals in recent months involving top AI developers that are flooding the booming AI sector with resources and money, and addressing resources -- such as electricity and infrastructure -- needed to support such technology.
